Subject: Re: [T2] steering wheel adjustment

> There is a punch park on the steering wheel under the button that
> matches a mark on the splined end of the shaft. Take a look and see if
> it's not. If not, then you are not factory aligned even if the steering
> wheel is centered properly.


The result of which is that you'll be able to turn the steering mechanisms
further in one direction then the other.  This can even eventually lead to
bending the mechanical stops in the system over time...after that, the
tires rub the suspension components at full lock.

...david

